    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="14"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d14">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/4528½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the British Special Mission</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Balfour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">4 May, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have just received a telegram
                    from the Foreign Office asking me to express the warm appreciation of His
                    Majesty’s Government for the important force of Destroyers already sent by the
                    United States Government to assist in our Naval operations and for their
                    generous intention to largely augment this force. This very timely and prompt
                    assistance will be invaluable.</p>
                <p>May I add a personal expression of my own thanks?</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arthur James Balfour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
